{{Korean name|[[Jeong (surname)|Chung]]}} {{Infobox person | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1934}} | nationality = [[South Korea]]n | occupation = [[Art history|Art historian]] | alma_mater = [[Seoul National University]] | employer = {{unbulleted list|[[Gyeongju National Museum]]|[[National Museum of Korea]]|[[Cultural Heritage Administration of Korea]]}} | module = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes | hangul = 정양모 | hanja = {{linktext|鄭|良|謨}} | mr = Chŏng Yangmo | rr = Jeong Yangmo}} }}
'''Chung Yangmo''' (born 1934) is a [[South Korea]]n [[art history|art historian]], known for his expertise in [[Korean pottery and porcelain|Korean ceramics]].
== Personal life == Chung Yangmo was born in 1934 as the fourth and final son of [[Chung Inbo]] ([[:ko:정인보|정인보]]; 鄭寅普), a historian and author during the [[Korea under Japanese rule|Japanese colonial period]].<ref name="Kyunghyang19840208">{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1984020800329202022&editNo=2&publishDate=1984-02-08&officeId=00032&pageNo=2&printNo=11804&publishType=00020&from=news|title=後孫漢學者爲堂鄭寅普 선생|trans-title=Classical scholar Widang Chung Inbo|work=[[Kyunghyang Sinmun]]|date=8 February 1984|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> He is an admirer of the works of Joseon Dynasty landscape painter [[Jeong Seon]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=103&oid=081&aid=0000076026|title=가슴속 그림 한폭: 정양모 전 국립중앙박물관장|trans-title=A painting in one's heart: former National Museum director Chung Yangmo|work=[[Seoul Sinmun]]|date=31 January 2006|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> He received his B.S. degree in History from [[Seoul National University]] in 1958.
Chung's [[divided family|family was divided]] by the [[Korean War]]: his father and elder sister Chung Kyung-wan were taken to [[North Korea]] in 1950. In 2004 he received news that Kyung-wan was still alive.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://legacy.www.hani.co.kr/section-003100000/2004/02/003100000200402121011283.html|title=북 누나 생존 확인한 정양모 위원장|trans-title=Commissioner Chung Yangmo's elder sister confirmed alive in North|work=[[Hankyoreh]]|date=12 February 2004|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> One of his other elder sisters, [[Chung Yang-wan]] ([[:ko:정양완|정양완]]), became a scholar of [[Korean literature]] with the [[Academy of Korean Studies]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jjan.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=189555|title=정양완교수 완역 정인보 '담원문록' 한글본 출간|trans-title=Professor Chung Yang-wan publishes complete hangul translation of Chung Inbo's 'Damwonmunrok'|work=Jeonbuk Ilbo|date=6 June 2015|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> He met the woman who would become his wife, [[Ewha Womans University]] student Lee Jung-won (이중원; 李仲瑗), in 1964 when she was preparing to write her thesis on pottery.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1996052500209121001&editNo=45&publishDate=1996-05-25&officeId=00020&pageNo=21&printNo=23205&publishType=00010&from=news|title=정양모(국립중앙 박물관장)—이중원씨|trans-title=Chung Yangmo (National Museum director) and Lee Jung-won|work=[[Dong-A Ilbo]]|date=25 May 1996|accessdate=19 May 2015}}</ref> He gave up on his plans to [[study abroad]] in order to marry her in 1967, and the couple went on to have two sons and a daughter.<ref name="Kyunghyang19840208"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.joins.com/article/3062109|title=鄭良謨 중앙박물관장 부인|trans-title=The wife of National Museum director Chung Yang-mo|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo]]|date=10 May 1995|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref>
Chung is a close friend of ceramicist [[Min Young-ki (artist)|Min Young-ki]] (민영기; 閔泳麒) and painter [[Chun Sung-woo]] (전성우; 全筬雨). In 1998, Min and Chun jointly made a [[Buncheong]]-style [[stoneware]] bowl for him, which is on display at the [[Asian Art Museum of San Francisco]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://searchcollection.asianart.org/view/objects/asitem/nid/15958|title=Collection details|publisher=Asian Art Museum Chong-Moon Lee Center for Asian Art and Culture|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref>
== Career == Chung began his career in the [[National Museum of Korea]] in 1962.<ref name="Kyunghyang19930326">{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1993032600329117013&editNo=12&publishDate=1993-03-26&officeId=00032&pageNo=17&printNo=14712&publishType=00010&from=news|title='외관보다 內實다질 차례' 鄭良謨 새 국립중앙박물관장|trans-title='Interior first, then exterior': Chung Yangmo, new National Museum of Korea director|work=Kyunghyang Sinmun|date=26 March 1993|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20090402/8715094/1|title=한국박물관 100년의 사람들: <4>정양모 前국립중앙박물관장|trans-title=100 years of Korean museums, #4: Chung Yangmo, former National Museum director|work=Dong-A Ilbo|date=2 April 2009|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> For much of his early career he worked under [[Choi Sun-u]] ([[:ko:최순우|최순우]]; 崔淳雨), then one of the country's foremost experts on [[Korean pottery and porcelain|Korean ceramics]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://koreana.kf.or.kr/view.asp?article_id=565&lang=English|title=Crepuscle on Cultural Past: Chung Yang-mo, Chief Curator, National Museum of Korea|work=Koreana Quarterly|date=Autumn 1991|volume=5|issue=3|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> In 1963, while holding the position of assistant researcher in the art department of the museum, he participated in fieldwork led by Choi in [[Yangju]], and discovered a [[kiln]] from the late [[Goryeo Dynasty]] in a village near [[Dobongsan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1963021200209207001&editNo=2&publishDate=1963-02-12&officeId=00020&pageNo=7&printNo=12703&publishType=00020&from=news|title=楊州에麗末의民間陶窯址|trans-title=In Yangju, a pottery kiln from the late Goryeo|work=Dong-A Ilbo|date=12 February 1963|accessdate=19 November 2015}} Accompanying photo: {{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1963021200209207005&editNo=2&publishDate=1963-02-12&officeId=00020&pageNo=7&printNo=12703&publishType=00020&from=news|title=발견자 鄭良謨씨|trans-title=Discoverer Chung Yangmo|work=Dong-A Ilbo|date=12 February 1963|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref>
From 1984 to 1986, Chung served as director of the [[Gyeongju National Museum]]. He went on to become the director of the [[National Museum of Korea]], serving from 1993 to 1999.<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=18 November 2015 | first1=Zixuan | last1=Zhang | url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/life/Mystery-of-the-cup-holder-30216913.html | title=Mystery of the cup holder | publisher=China Daily | website=The nation}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=103&oid=001&aid=0004487116|title=정양모 중앙박물관장 사표제출|trans-title=National Museum director Chung Yangmo submits resignation|work=[[Yonhap News]]|date=14 December 1999|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> In May 2003, he was appointed as the new commissioner of the [[Cultural Heritage Administration of Korea]]'s Cultural Properties Commission.<ref name="Donga20030515">{{cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=103&oid=020&aid=0000187663|title=문화재위원장 정양모 박사 '문화재는 새로 만들수 없죠'|trans-title=Cultural Properties Commissioner Chung Yangmo: 'cultural heritage cannot be remade anew'|work=Dong-A Ilbo|date=15 May 2003|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> He served in that position until 2005, when he was succeeded by Seoul National University professor [[Ahn Hwi-joon]] (안휘준; 安輝濬).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=103&oid=096&aid=0000017175|title=문화재위원장에 서울대 안휘준 교수 선출|trans-title=Seoul National University professor Ahn Hwi-joon chosen as Cultural Properties Commissioner|work=[[Seoul Broadcasting System]]|date=6 May 2005|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref>
==Awards and honours== In 2005, Chung received the Silver Crown of the [[Order of Cultural Merit (Korea)|Order of Cultural Merit]] from the government of South Korea.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=200512051819471&code=100100|title=정양모 前관장 은관문화훈장 서훈|trans-title=Former director Chung Yangmo receives Silver Crown of the Order of Cultural Merit|work=Kyunghyang Sinmun|date=5 December 2005|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> In 2013 his fellow scholars published a [[Festschrift]] in his honour to celebrate his eightieth year of life (in [[East Asian age reckoning]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.kmib.co.kr/article/view.asp?arcid=0007281641&code=11110000|title=정양모 전 국립중앙박물관장 '한국 깊이있게 알리려면 문화재 보여줘야'|trans-title=Chung Yangmo, former National Museum director: 'To let people know Korea deeply, protect its cultural heritage'|work=[[Kukmin Ilbo]]|date=16 June 2013|accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref>
