'''Idzi Jan Panic''' (born 1952 in [[Wodzisław Śląski]]) is [[Poland|Polish]] [[historian]], professor at the [[University of Silesia]]. He is specializing in history of [[Cieszyn Silesia]] and medieval Poland.
He graduated from the University of Silesia in 1976 and gained a Ph.D. from this university in 1980. In 1999 Panic gained the title of professor.
His articles were published in "[[Studia Historyczne]]", "[[Sobótka. Śląski Kwartalnik Historyczny]]", "[[Pamiętnik Cieszyński]]" and "[[Těšínsko (magazine)|Těšínsko]]".
